{"questionId":"33025403","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider the palindromic polynomial <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>4</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>This polynomial can be expressed in the form</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>u</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>v</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>u</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>u</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>v</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>By forming and solving an appropriate system of equations in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>u</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi></math>, determine the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>u</mi></math> and the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p>attempts to expand the product of two quadratic factors&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong><em> (M1)<br><br></em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>4</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>u</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>v</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>u</mi><mi>v</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>u</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>v</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)<br><br></strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>4</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>u</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>v</mi></mrow></mfenced><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>u</mi><mi>v</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>u</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>v</mi></mrow></mfenced><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)<br><br></strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p>equates coefficients and forms a system of two equations in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>u</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>u</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math> &nbsp; and&nbsp;&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>u</mi><mi>v</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>u</mi><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p>attempts to solve their system of two equations&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>u</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math> &nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Candidates must attempt to form and solve a system of equations in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>u</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi></math>. Hence, award no marks for working backwards from either decimal or exact values of roots given by a GDC.</p>\n<p>Award <strong><em>A0</em></strong> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>u</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>u</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math> both specified.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>attempts to divide one of&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>u</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; or&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>v</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; into&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)<br><br></strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>for example, the quotient is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>u</mi></mrow></mfenced><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>u</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>u</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p>sets their quotient equal to&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>v</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>u</mi></mrow></mfenced><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>u</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>u</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>v</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>u</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>u</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math> &nbsp; and&nbsp;&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>u</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>v</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempts to solve their equations for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>u</mi></math> and then <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi></math> (or vice versa)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)<br><br></strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>for example, the remainder is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>u</mi><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>u</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>u</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>u</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>u</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p>sets their remainder equal to zero&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempts to solve for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>u</mi></math>(or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi></math>)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>u</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>3</mn></math> &nbsp; and &nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>u</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>A1<br><br></strong></p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>u</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math> &nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A0</strong></em> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>u</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>u</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math> both specified.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 3</strong></p>\n<p>considers&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math>, for example&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>u</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mi>v</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>considers <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced></math>, for example&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>&nbsp;(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>u</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>v</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>33</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempts to solve their system of two equations&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>u</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math> &nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <strong><em>A0</em></strong> for&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>u</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math>&nbsp; and&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>u</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; both specified.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong><em>[6 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"33025403","referenceCode":"24N.3.AHL.TZ0.2f","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"By forming and solving an appropriate system of equations in u and v, determine the value of u and the value of v.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"f","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 6]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.12—Factor and remainder theorems, sum and product of roots","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.16—Solution of systems of linear equations"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}